SUMMARY:Brown County Art Guild 2026 Annual Raffle
DESCRIPTION:Take a chance to win ‘Painters Point’, a beautiful original oil painting generously donated by Guild Artist, Allen Hutton. He strives to render the fleeting patterns of light and shadow with the simple purpose of preserving the reality of a landscape at a particular moment in time and season. Allen has achieved numerous awards and his art can be found in both private and corporate collections across the county.   \nTickets:  1 for $30, 2 for $50, or 5 for $100   \nYour generosity helps the Guild to preserve its historic collection, promote its award-winning artist members, and offer workshops and programs throughout the year!  \nThe drawing of the winning raffle ticket will be held at 3pm on Saturday, November 21, 2026, at the Guild.  \nThe winner need not be present for the drawing.  \nPurchase options: \nIn person at the Guild, call 812-988-6185 or purchase raffle tickets at:  \nhttps://browncountyartguild.org/product/brown-county-art-guild-annual-raffle/ \n————————————————————————————————————————- \nBrown County Art Guild – PO Box 324 – 48 S. Van Buren St. Nashville, Indiana 47448 – Ph# 812-988-6185 \n– A not-for-profit organization located in the heart of downtown Nashville, Indiana. On display throughout its galleries is a prized collection of historic paintings as well as current works for sale from regional award-winning member artists.  Throughout the year, the Guild offers artist demonstrations, workshops, and special exhibits.   \nGuild hours: March-December 2026, Monday – Saturday, 11 – 5 and Sunday, 12 – 4 or by appointment. \n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/brown-county-art-guild-2026-annual-raffle/
