SUMMARY:New Exhibitions at the Brown County Art Guild!
DESCRIPTION:March 20 – July 17, 2026 \nGuild Artist Exhibition and Sale \nSpring brings renewal, creativity, and fresh inspiration. Join us for the Guild Artist Exhibition & Sale showcasing new works from our Guild Artist Members. Experience the beauty of the season through painting, color, and artistic expression. \n \n \nMarch 20 – July 17, 2026 \nNature’s Symphony \nSpecial Exhibition & Sale \nDiscover Nature’s Symphony – Special Exhibition & Sale featuring artwork by our talented Guild Artists. Experience how each artist interprets the beauty, rhythm, and movement of nature—capturing the harmony of landscapes, light, color, and season in their own unique voice. \n\nBrown County Art Guild – A not for profit organization located in the heart of downtown Nashville, Indiana.  On display throughout its galleries is a prized collection of historic paintings as well as current works for sale from regional award-winning member artists.  The Guild also offers artist demonstrations, workshops, and a variety of events and programs throughout the year.   \nMarch – December: Monday–Saturday, 11 – 5 and Sunday, 12 – 4  \nWINTER HOURS: January – February: Thursday – Saturday 11 – 5 and Sunday 12-4 or by appointment. \nFor more information, please call the Guild at 812-988-6185 or visit our website: https://browncountyartguild.org/ \n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/new-exhibitions-at-the-brown-county-art-guild/
