TRANSP:OPAQUE
SUMMARY:Dances With Dirt Race
DESCRIPTION:For those of you unfamiliar with Brown County, Indiana, the terrain will bring you shock and awe! Vicious 600’ ridges, breathtaking natural beauty and wicked trails abound. Gnaw Bone is about one mile out of Nashville, IN, an artisan community with over 200 galleries. A picture postcard of a town and definitely worth a visit, just 3 miles from the race start.\n\nThe course is a wild, unpredictable adventure that takes runners through rugged trails, steep climbs, and creek crossings throughout Brown County State Park and Yellowwood State Forest. With its challenging terrain and jaw-dropping scenery, it’s equal parts trail race and test of your grit, guaranteed to leave you muddy, tired, and grinning ear to ear!\n\n\nOf all the events, the 10K has the most extreme, insane terrain, billed as the worlds toughest. All other individual events will give you a beautiful trail run experience, the 10k will beat you to a pulp and make the warrior/mudder kind of races seem hokey and artificial. The DWD Gnaw Bone 10K will prove that the extremes that lie out there in nature are where it’s at!\n\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/dances-with-dirt-race/
CATEGORIES:Happening,Outdoor Adventure,Races
LOCATION:Brown County
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://browncounty.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Untitled-design-54.jpg
END:VEVENT
