SUMMARY:Classic Camp
DESCRIPTION:Relive (or experience for the first time) the magic of summer camp! Designed for adults 50+, this experience is a mix of all the classic camp fun, including campfires, s’mores, canoeing, hiking, arts & crafts, and swimming and a chaplain led program.\nAfter a full day at camp, relax in comfort! You’ll stay in hotel-style rooms at the Conference Center, complete with real beds, private bathrooms, and air conditioning.\n\n\nJuly 31-August 3, 2026\n\n\nCheck-in: 4-6pm\n\n\nCheck-out: 10am\n\n\nThis program runs Friday – Monday. We encourage all participants to stay for the full experience, but we understand that some may need to leave early. If you need to depart early please select the Friday–Sunday afternoon option (departing before dinner on Sunday) during registration so we can plan accordingly.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAges 45+\n\n\nProgram Rates\n\n\nAttendance cost is calculated during online registration, depending on your lodging selection. Rates are per person and include program fees, lodging and meals.\n\n\nConference Center – Single Occupancy: $75 per person\n\n\nConference Center – Double Occupancy: $75 per person\n\n\n\n\n\n\n
